Edwin Dixon (ejd83 76241975) & Jianqiao Guo jgu56


1. Open terminal in directory ESlab/ence260-ucfk4/assignment/final

2. enter command "make program".

3. Text on the ucfk matrix display will be shown saying "welcome".

4. Press button1 to start the game.

5. A pattern representing a paper wil now be displayed.

6. To change selection use the navswitch. up (North) is paper, down (South) is rock and right (West) is scissors.

7. To select which one of the three yu want to play against your opponent use left (East) on the navswitch which will send your selection to your opponent's board.

8. After a countdown followed by your selection a result will be shown on the board with either "WIN", "DRAW", "LOSE" or "ERROR". If "ERROR" is shown it is likely caused by interference in the IR transmission   

9. Pressing button1 will restart the game.
